[1] USA: embargo delays Cuban Ebola doctors pay
Date: Sat 13 Dec 2014
Source: Aljazeera [edited]
http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/12/us-embargo-delays-ebola-doctors-pay-from-cuba-2014121312469991605.html


Cuba had to cover food and lodging expenses for dozens of its doctors fighting Ebola in Sierra Leone after the US embargo delayed payments from the World Health Organization (WHO), Luis Di Fabio, the WHO representative for Cuba, told The Associated Press news agency on Fri 12 Dec 2014.

It had to request special licenses from the US Treasury Department to transfer money to the doctors in Africa. The licenses were eventually granted, and the Cuban government-employed doctors only recently received payments dating as far back as October [2014], he said.

Di Fabio said there were relatively minor delays in opening accounts for the doctors in Guinea and Liberia, but those have been resolved.

