& Roger Feldman <promedrf@gmail.com>

[We have read about non-payment of salaries for local health workers in the 3 countries, but it is unexpected to hear that some international aid workers have not been paid for months. Cuban doctors get the equivalent of USD 70 per month back home, but were to receive USD 250 per month for food and accommodation in West Africa.

The Cuban doctors in Guinea have not yet been deployed because they do not speak French, and only 2 interpreters are available for their in-country training; see ProMED post Ebola virus disease - ex Africa (49): Cuba, liability, Emory case notes, susp. 20141210.3025601. - Mod.JW]

